der=0><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Character Level</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>18 - 24</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Solo/Group</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Solo</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Zone</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>East Karana</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>XP</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>9</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Loot</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>3</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Danger</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>5</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Mob</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Crag Spider</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Mob Level</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>18 - 20</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Location</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>-1500  -3000</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Factions</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Not known</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Spells Used</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Engulfing Darkness, Heart Flutter, Heat Blood, Fear, Leach</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Strategy</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Crag spiders are found through the East Karana zone.  They have a wicked poison and hit extremely hard, so a 16th level pet can easily be consumed if you're not careful.<br><br>

Toward the south end of the zone there is a fishing village.  Park yourself and your pets somewhere in the center of the buildings, a bit away from the hill.  Face north, toward the hill, and pull a crag spider down.  Occasionally, you will find them wandering about to the West or East.  Be VERY careful of the Hill Giants that roam over this hill, they come down to the empty buildings, but do not tend to pass them into the area you will be fighting.  Use of Fear, however, can bring some close calls, so just be aware.<br><br>

Cast Engulfing Darkness.  It is sometimes resisted, but the spiders run slowly. If it is resisted get as far back as you can and try again. You can tell your partner to hit with it if you're too close.  Hit with Heart Flutter while your partner hits with Heat Blood. Pets should be engaged by now.  One partner hits with fear while the other applies another DoT.  The spider might be aggro to one of you by now, but it's slowed enough to kite until the Fear takes hold.  Continue to apply Fear, an occasional Leach or Lifedraw, and watch it die.  If you do not apply fear one pet will surely die.  Since bones are hard to come by in the Karanas this is not a real good situation.  Do not, at any time, melee these guys.  Their poison is strong enough to bring you down hard, especially if you didn't get Leach off.  This wouldn't be so bad, really, if it weren't for the wandering lions and wolves.  They are a real pain if they jump in while you are at the end of combat. Griffawns also roam through the area.  They're easy to kill, but hit extremely hard and can take a pet out faster than you can blink at it. Keep clear of them if you can.<br><br>

Carrion spiders in the area are indifferent to you, and usually green, but will attack if they are very close to combat with your Crag Spider. The experience for these guys is great. Loot ranges from many Spider Silk, some Venom Sacs, Spider Legs, occasional Words, Runes, Grimoire pages.</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Author</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'><a href ='mailto:ianubis@nether-world.com'>Oniuan</td></tr><tr></table><br><br><table border='0' width=611><tr><td width='100%' colspan='2' bgcolor='#21456B'><p align='left' style='word-spacing: 0; margin: 0'><b><font color='#FFFFFF' size='2' face='Tahoma'>Additional Comments</font></b></td></tr><td width='17%'><font color='#FFFFFF' size='2' face='Tahoma'>Tebon Undeadmaster</font></td><td width='83%'><font color='#FFFFFF' size='2' face='Tahoma'>I have hunted these spiders from 20th to 24th level. What I found to work best was to start with darkness and send my pet. Then cast Fear until it sticks, stack Heart Flutter and Heat Blood. Then follow the Crag until the fear breaks or it dies. (you can life tap to get health back as needed) Re-apply Fear as needed. Watch pet for poison and heal as needed. The poison from these spiders if REALLY nasty and you can lose a lot of pets if your not careful. You can make a lot of money of these spiders, just put a few points into the tailor skill and buy a 2 slot sewing kit, then combine the spider silk into silk swatches. Many high level tailors will come to this zone to buy silk swatches. The going price is 5gp per silk or 1 pp per silk swatch. If you combine 2 spider silks in the sewing kit, it makes a swatch, the swatches will stack in groups of 20. I 400+ plat in 2 weeks hunting here. The Crags will drop from 0 to 8 spider silks at a time. Still getting exp. at 24th level, but its much slower. Time to move onto the druids. ;)</font></td></tr></table></td></table></div>